Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.43,0:00:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not gonna make this easy,\Nare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.13,0:00:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately,\Nas much as I admire your spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.92,0:00:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ca ne change rien.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.31,0:00:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Subject anesthetized with\N0.5 cc's of sodium pentobarbital.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.84,0:00:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Transfected with human\Nhepatic cancer cells,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.93,0:00:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,underwent six rounds of\Nintra-abdominal treatment with ES-22.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:51.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vertical incision\Nthrough the rectus sheath
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.12,0:00:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,opens the abdominal cavity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.36,0:00:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Incision extended into the-thorax.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.35,0:01:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liver appears normal in color.\NNo apparent scarring or...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.33,0:01:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.90,0:01:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cancerous tumor still\Npresent on the right lobe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.97,0:01:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1.12 centimeters in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.52,0:01:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No reduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House S03E03\NInformed Consent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.94,0:02:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,71 years old,\Ncancer research specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.95,0:02:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minor tremors,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.49,0:02:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,localized melanoma removed two years\Nago, cataracts. And he can't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.41,0:02:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, disregard the facial lacerations.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're creepy,\Nbut unfortunately irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.66,0:02:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.83,0:02:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have your cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, why the lacerations are creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:03:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was about to dissect one\Nof his lab rats when he collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The little vermin seized the day, so\Nto speak, and went medieval on his ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.93,0:03:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What? My fly open?\N- So the pain's returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.13,0:03:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no pain, he was unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.16,0:03:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing because\Nhe wasn't able to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.06,0:03:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We're talking about you.\N- Obviously. I'm obviously not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.68,0:03:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it with you people?\NI don't use the cane, you're shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.27,0:03:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I use the cane...\N- We're just concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the wrong person. I can breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ezra Powell,\Non the other hand, is gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.50,0:03:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The Ezra Powell?\N- Researcher?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.44,0:03:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The guy who wrote that textbook?\N- Not that textbook, the textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. There's actually\Nanother doctor you admire?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I admire lots of doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.50,0:03:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, most of them look a lot\Nbetter in knee socks than Ezra Powell,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.48,0:03:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but seeing as they can all breathe...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.09,0:03:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oxygenation is through the floor,\Nand lungs are full of fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta be his heart.\NCould be amyloidosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.68,0:03:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or his lungs, probably from years\Nof inhaling toxic chemicals in his lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.24,0:03:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not the lungs, chest x-ray's clean.\N- So's his EKG, it's not his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're being too nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.37,0:03:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Outside the hospital, he can't breathe,\Ninside the hospital, he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we help. At least,\Nenough to screw with our test results.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.04,0:04:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Source of the problem's\Neither in his heart or his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.18,0:04:08.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So all we gotta do is stop helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.63,0:04:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put a little pressure on him,\Nand see which gives out first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.07,0:04:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At 71, we get his heart\Nor lungs to give out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.76,0:04:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we might not get 'em to give in again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're gonna\Ndo it in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.27,0:04:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put him on an incline treadmill,\Nand do a stress EKG.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So much for the admiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get you started.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.56,0:04:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll turn your oxygen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I worked with Williams on the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.41,0:04:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,first protocol for this machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone still uses it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except for Williams.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.08,0:04:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He died four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.13,0:04:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was 84.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He died parasailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was always an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.80,0:04:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there, you know\Nthe protocol's only a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.40,0:05:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His heart rate's flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.78,0:05:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't get it past 130,\Nwe're not gonna see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if he falls and breaks a hip,\Nwe're not gonna see anything either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except an increase in\Nour malpractice insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured House might\Ngo back to the pills, but
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.27,0:05:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if he's using his cane,\Nhe's right back to where he was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.50,0:05:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.70,0:05:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luckily, he'll handle it in a stoic,\Ngrown-up fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.85,0:05:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never take it out on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.94,0:05:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.35,0:05:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've-- I gotta stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.79,0:05:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.34,0:05:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heart rate's only 90,\NI'm gonna increase the incline.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I  gotta stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.54,0:05:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I- I've gotta get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.13,0:05:50.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing great,\Njust a little faster, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-- I don't need a cheerleader,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.29,0:05:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop. This isn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.49,0:06:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His heart rate barely got above 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't breathe,\Nthere's too much fluid in his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.06,0:06:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.27,0:06:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got fluid in his lungs?\NWhatever are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.94,0:06:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, now I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.07,0:06:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put him on a treadmill, and\Nrun him like one of his rats on a wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't run, he can hardly walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.28,0:06:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's 'cause he's\Nnot trying hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.98,0:06:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he was, his heart rate would go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.47,0:06:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exercising with a lungful of\Nyour own bodily fluids tends to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't call it\Na stress test for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.45,0:06:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do it again.\N- He's drowning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.33,0:06:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then pull him out of the pool,\Nand do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.91,0:06:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm assuming this isn't\Nyour idea of a long-term solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.35,0:06:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get rid of the fluid in your\Nlungs so you'll be able to do the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.51,0:06:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To see if it's my heart or my lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.67,0:06:44.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.97,0:06:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My money's on both.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.48,0:06:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been in and out of\Nthe hospital for the past year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.52,0:06:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm old, I'm sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.94,0:06:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting older, and sicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.05,0:06:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not a very interesting\Ndifferential, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.05,0:07:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need a $400 handbag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's kinda hard to check your throat\Nwhen you're flapping your gums around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.23,0:07:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's for the fall formal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't care if it's\Nfor the presidential inauguration.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.73,0:07:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm using Marissa's old dress.\NIt's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.40,0:07:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you know what else is free?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.27,0:07:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roof over your head, the food you eat,\Nyour phone, your computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.66,0:07:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long have you been congested?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A week, ever since\Nwe got back from Fresno.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.34,0:07:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fresno? That's in France, right?\NSee the Parthenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.17,0:07:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, California.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.15,0:07:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got no appetite,\NI'm aching all over, I'm weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.91,0:07:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Does that hurt?\N- Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.67,0:07:48.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does his voice always have\Nthat unattractive nasal tone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.26,0:07:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.99,0:07:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna take that giggle as a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.44,0:07:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fever,  aches,\Nweakness, loss of appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.22,0:08:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Been having any anal\Nsex with IV drug users lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.11,0:08:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of  course not, I'm married.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you think he might've been--\N- No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a rhinovirus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.65,0:08:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.98,0:08:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.95,0:08:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this four times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and stay off airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're flying cesspools.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.83,0:08:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You dropped something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.69,0:08:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's anything else\Nyou can think of, please call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.00,0:08:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.85,0:08:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's too old and weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.05,0:08:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this is way, way better.\NThis'll work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.85,0:08:48.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, just try.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are 20 words to describe
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.94,0:08:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,chest pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burning,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.96,0:08:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,squeezing,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.40,0:08:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stabbing, tearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.24,0:08:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each one diagnostically useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.95,0:09:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, you have to thank Dr.\NPowell's textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.09,0:09:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no words to describe\Ndegrees of what he's feeling right now--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.95,0:09:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shortness of breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.49,0:09:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had worked on those issues,\Nthere would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause he would never have\Ngiven up until he had an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.48,0:09:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. House.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.23,0:09:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.56,0:09:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you're very busy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.05,0:09:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm just gonna try\Nand speed things up a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.20,0:09:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that epi? That's not the protocol.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.14,0:09:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the protocol is what\Nyou tried to do and failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.54,0:09:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,each time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.40,0:09:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up over 100.\NNow we're getting somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.54,0:09:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's it look, Foreman?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.77,0:09:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No EKG changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Then we push harder.\N- House, you're gonna kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.98,0:09:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.16,0:09:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let him do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.14,0:09:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? That's why he doesn't\Nhave to wear knee socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,130.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.68,0:10:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our magic number.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing here. Foreman?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.22,0:10:06.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still no sign of blockages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's not the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.91,0:10:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it must be the lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.79,0:10:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Wasn't so hard, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.47,0:10:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Just give me the\Nrest of the epinephrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Test is over,\Nit's okay, we're gonna stabilize you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.22,0:10:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, just let me die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.16,0:10:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're not gonna die.\N- Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll find a treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.68,0:10:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna live like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.43,0:10:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He says no more tests, he wants to\Ndie and he wants us to help him do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.18,0:10:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I want to play a little game I like\Nto call block my spike with misty may.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.63,0:10:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's thought this through,\Nit's not an impulsive decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.01,0:10:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither is mine. He's depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.01,0:11:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll feel much better\Nafter we cure him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.68,0:11:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's seen all the tests we've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.30,0:11:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we figure out what's causing the\Nlung damage, it's too late to reverse it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.58,0:11:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't know that without\Nknowing what's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's his call.\N- So, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.97,0:11:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put a plastic bag over\Nhis head and get it over with?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.22,0:11:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we give him a\Nsyringe full of morphine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.06,0:11:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every doctor I've ever\Npracticed with has done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.62,0:11:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't want to, they don't like to,\Nbut that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.21,0:11:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't, I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.06,0:11:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't do it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.19,0:11:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just said we should\Nrespect his decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Respect it doesn't\Nnecessarily mean we honor it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.72,0:11:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. It just means we talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.66,0:11:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At some point, "do no harm" has to\Nmean allowing nature to take its course,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.23,0:11:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not stubbornly standing\Nin the way of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.00,0:11:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sticking a metal syringe into a plastic\NIV line and pumping in a lethal dose
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.69,0:11:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of morphine is not letting\Nnature take its course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not according to\Nthe state of New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's better we allow him\Nto slowly suffocate in his own plasma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.90,0:11:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose side are you on, senator?\NFirst respect his wishes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.12,0:11:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then invade Iraq, then get\Nthe troops home... make up your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.75,0:11:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly a lot of interesting\Nthings to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:01.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stress EKG rules out the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.44,0:12:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means something's gotta\Nbe attacking his lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.54,0:12:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mycoplasma or strep pneumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.60,0:12:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is,\Nit's too late to do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.31,0:12:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We could try levofloxacin.\N- Coming up with a new treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.48,0:12:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't gonna do us any good unless\Nwe convince him it's worth trying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.93,0:12:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.20,0:12:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he's old, sick, tiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.95,0:12:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can do whatever we want to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.34,0:12:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've fallen out of\Nbed and got the nasal cannula
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.62,0:12:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- wrapped around his neck somehow.\N- Ezra, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.50,0:12:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to live hooked to machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.74,0:12:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too we-- too weak to wipe my own ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you want to wipe your own ass,\Nwhen you could have someone do it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wasting your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.74,0:12:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be other patients\Nyou could actually help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.14,0:12:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, all services rendered\Non a first come, first served basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't consent to any more tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.89,0:13:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if anyone tries\Nto so much as touch me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.67,0:13:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll press charges for assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.14,0:13:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, well, you heard the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.43,0:13:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He  wants everyone to leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go first?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.37,0:13:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.04,0:13:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you'd have the\Nguts to do what had to be done
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if it came to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.61,0:13:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're nowhere near that.\NIt's time to test your lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.00,0:13:43.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.12,0:13:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna have to exhale sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Stop!\N- House, you're hurting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.30,0:13:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're hurting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.94,0:13:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.08,0:13:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to help us,\Nwe don't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your lungs slowly fill with fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.23,0:14:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gasp to catch every breath,\Nbut never can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.57,0:14:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every breath is petrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.30,0:14:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be slow,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,painful,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,torturous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.41,0:14:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't choose our birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.89,0:14:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And we don't choose our death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.06,0:14:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if you could?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How 'bout we make a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.68,0:14:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You give me one more day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.31,0:14:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't find out exactly\Nwhat's wrong with you by then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.49,0:14:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.72,0:14:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,24 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.84,0:14:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, it's not gonna kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old guy, lungs, fluid, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.83,0:14:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You cannot help him kill himself.\N- Of course I can,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.03,0:14:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chase says we do it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.48,0:14:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Cuddy's not gonna let you.\N- Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.19,0:15:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want me to kill him, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.70,0:15:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a big shock.\NI don't want to kill him either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How  do I not kill him?\NBy you guys doing your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.28,0:15:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have 24 hours to figure\Nout what's wrong with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.19,0:15:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tick-tock, tick-tock!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.25,0:15:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw cultures. Pneumonia.\NShould be bacteria in his blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's gonna take longer than 24h.\N- Not if I spin down the sample.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.84,0:15:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separate off the buffy coat,\Nthen gram stain for bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, do an amylase, d-dimer,\Nc-reactive peptide, get a urine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.14,0:15:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and do a bronchial\Nsputum while you're at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.31,0:15:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, check his home and\Nlab for radiation and toxins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.79,0:15:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And do a bone marrow biopsy.\N- All of that in 24 hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.78,0:15:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, whatever you don't get done,\Nyou can finish at the autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.27,0:16:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys look like crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you got?\N- Purple dye on my fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.69,0:16:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What'd the bone marrow biopsy show?\N- Don't have the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.24,0:17:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?\NWhat have you been doing all night?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.25,0:17:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jell-o shots and wild sex, what else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no bacteria\Nin the blood cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still have some cooking,\Nbut so far nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.63,0:17:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in the urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lab was clean enough to\Ndo surgery in because, well, they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.12,0:17:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no sign of viruses\Nor fleas on any of the rats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.03,0:17:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, tell her to call a clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.01,0:17:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell her to leave a message,\Nand I'll get back to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.16,0:17:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tell her to leave\Na personal message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.99,0:17:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who's that?\N- Your protégé?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.42,0:17:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.67,0:17:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dictation tapes, he records everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.60,0:17:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.27,0:17:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Because he's a diligent researcher?\N- Or he's losing his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.53,0:17:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lot of people dictate their notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.94,0:17:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we could assume that,\Nand we'd have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.06,0:17:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or we could assume it's a symptom,\Nin which case,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.05,0:17:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whatever's in his lungs\Nis also in his brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.78,0:17:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you got something more promising.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'll go get an MRI of his head.\N- Keep testing until you find something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.19,0:17:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to my office\Nto rest for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:18:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time\Nsince I took an anatomy class,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm pretty sure you're moving\Nfarther and farther away from my lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.99,0:18:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running out of places to look,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.67,0:18:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't mean we're gonna stop looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.58,0:18:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, no, not for six more hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.13,0:18:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You want us to fail?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.05,0:18:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No abnormal nuclei means no leukemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.92,0:18:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- He a drinker?\N- Not according to the history.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.29,0:18:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, yes, he drinks,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.45,0:18:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which gives us a nice, mundane\Nexplanation for the acellularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.37,0:18:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or he's telling the truth. Which\Nmeans fungus is still on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.46,0:18:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But your entire view of\Nhuman nature gets destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.45,0:18:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six of one, half a dozen of the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad news fast.\NGood news, you can take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Head's clean, you were wrong,\Nhis faculties are intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.99,0:18:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.96,0:18:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If his brain was addled, we wouldn't\Nhave to listen to anything he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.83,0:18:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand me the 10% KOH.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.62,0:18:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 4:00, we have nothing to tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.29,0:19:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we have no reason to talk to him.\NStill haven't ruled out fungus.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.23,0:19:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, we have, no bugs, no hyphae.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,next procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.63,0:19:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We sneak in,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,turn back the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whole team.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:21.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Must be bad news.\N- Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.42,0:19:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bone marrow biopsy\Nrevealed multiple myeloma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.35,0:19:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not good news,\Nbut there are some treatments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.99,0:19:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- We have to draw some blood.\N- What about my breathing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.63,0:19:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Associated hyperviscosity syndrome gummed\Nup the blood vessels in your lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Chase said my calcium is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.13,0:19:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm, we call him Dr. Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no M protein in my urine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Odd presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.18,0:19:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So odd that Dr. Cameron doesn't--\Ndoesn't believe it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:19:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Just give me 12 more hours.\N- We had a deal. No more tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.43,0:20:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.09,0:20:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme six more hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.06,0:20:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, there is no evidence\Nthat you are terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.70,0:20:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You a man of your word or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.65,0:20:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, as a matter of fact, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.47,0:20:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then discharge me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My lungs will slowly fill with fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.45,0:20:22.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll gasp to catch every breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.93,0:20:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But never can.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every breath will be petrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.57,0:20:27.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be slow,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.74,0:20:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,painful,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,torturous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.01,0:20:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're  really gonna\Nlet me die like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.55,0:21:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where you going?\N- Nowhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody who can walk\Nshould get outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.75,0:21:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You can't do that.\N- Can't do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.44,0:21:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Administer a prescription painkiller\Nto a patient who's in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.19,0:21:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure somebody sees\Nyou downstairs in the cafeteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.78,0:21:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.31,0:21:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either I die in pain, or I just die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.95,0:21:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.42,0:21:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what the argument is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.01,0:22:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's about whether you die,\Nor we murder you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.53,0:22:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's gonna happen here is that someone\Nis getting a buttload of morphine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.09,0:22:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure exactly who at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.24,0:22:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be a part of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.02,0:22:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.77,0:22:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.69,0:22:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,exactly what was on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.66,0:23:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getting a laryngoscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.68,0:23:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Don't just stand there, help.\N- But you told him--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.36,0:23:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was something I like to call a lie.\NBad, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.99,0:23:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's way further\Ndown the list than murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.91,0:24:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's unconscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.48,0:24:03.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no more whining.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.23,0:24:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep testing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.58,0:24:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go get a ventilator.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.61,0:24:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do this all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.20,0:24:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can legally assume
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.49,0:24:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he'd consent to whatever a\Nreasonable person would consent to.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.38,0:24:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a reasonable person\Nwould obviously consent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.60,0:24:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to being put in a coma against their\Nwill just to satisfy your curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.94,0:24:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I try to kill him, you're mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.87,0:24:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't kill him, you're mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.53,0:24:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- All he wanted was some dignity.\N- Were you in that room with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.33,0:24:42.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he wearing a tux while\Nhe was choking on his own plasma?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.70,0:24:45.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep doing the tests.\NTake your time, do it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.73,0:24:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.63,0:24:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.08,0:24:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.33,0:24:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cameron, why'd you do these cuts\Nso far down on this MRI of his head?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.85,0:25:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to get his\Nbrain stem and his c-spine,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.80,0:25:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,make sure his diaphragm\Nwasn't paralyzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.65,0:25:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You also caught the top of his lungs.\NThere's scarring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.81,0:25:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do know that you can't\Nreally pierce me with your stares?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.52,0:25:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lung scarring, along with the bad bone\Nmarrow, points to an autoimmune disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.90,0:25:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Could be pulmonary fibrosis.\N- Or lupus.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.18,0:25:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can kill himself\Nafter we get him better.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.21,0:25:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start him on an IVIG for the lupus,\Nand get a colonoscopy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.15,0:25:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lupus could be hiding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.05,0:25:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.41,0:25:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drama queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.12,0:25:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Descending colon's clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.24,0:25:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moving into the sigmoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.26,0:25:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure could use a little\Nmore help around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.75,0:25:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's doing what she believes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.34,0:25:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if she was acting on principle,\Nshe'd be in here trying to stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.04,0:25:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All she's doing is running away\Nfrom the principle so she won't have
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.82,0:25:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- to feel uncomfortable facing it.\N- And if you were acting on principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.79,0:26:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you would've called the cops when\Nyou thought House was killing the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.22,0:26:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.80,0:26:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.15,0:26:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think she's gonna have\Na problem deciding what to tell Cuddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.82,0:26:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O² sats 89 and dropping.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.85,0:26:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were only supposed\Nto put on a pound a week during
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.41,0:26:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- your last trimester.\N- I'm not pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.24,0:26:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about your little\Nstunt with Dr. Powell.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.31,0:26:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really a stunt.\NMore of a trick, a ruse, a hoodwink.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.52,0:26:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- A lie.\N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.49,0:26:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lying is sometimes good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.56,0:26:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like when you're trying to teach someone\Na lesson about humility or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.19,0:26:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I'm trying to do is save his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.73,0:26:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not gonna learn anything. I just\Nthought the same principle might apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.80,0:26:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It does.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.60,0:26:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've just let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.19,0:26:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not gonna get sued\Nfor keeping him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.24,0:26:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.54,0:26:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We completely disregarded his wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.52,0:26:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to disagree with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.66,0:26:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Want me to yell at you?\N- It is comforting.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.74,0:26:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're doctors.\NWe treat patients, we don't kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.41,0:27:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How right you are, Dr. Cuddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.90,0:27:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We also don't pad our bills,\Nswipe samples from the pharmacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.11,0:27:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or fantasize about the teenage\Ndaughters of our patients either.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.05,0:27:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True, better be true, and you're a pig.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.56,0:27:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry about your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.77,0:27:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we really should spend\Nsome time talking about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.72,0:27:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The IVIG made him worse.\NO² sats plummeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.74,0:27:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we know it's not lupus.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.01,0:27:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.25,0:27:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.57,0:27:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gonna need an open\Nlung biopsy to confirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.57,0:27:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So now we're gonna operate on the guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.80,0:27:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless you've invented a new\Nway of doing an open lung biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.02,0:27:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you searched Dr. Powell's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.29,0:27:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you find a copy of the january\N1967 Massachusetts medical journal?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.40,0:27:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.13,0:27:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just figured,\Nif you're not doing any work,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.62,0:27:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you might like something\Nto pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.93,0:27:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Centerfold's a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.43,0:28:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's your leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.60,0:28:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.82,0:28:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gonna keep on hurting.\NYou're gonna keep on asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.19,0:28:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's Ezra Powell?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.44,0:28:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resting comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.15,0:28:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, that's not what Cameron says.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.23,0:28:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate practicing\Nmedicine in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.38,0:28:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not asking you to help him\Nkill himself. He's just asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.12,0:28:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The disease will kill him.\N- I know what he was asking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.16,0:28:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I just said no.\N- You've done it before.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.34,0:28:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plenty of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.50,0:28:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To patients that I knew were terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.65,0:28:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, give me a break. This\Nhas nothing to do with saving a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.46,0:28:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just can't bear the\Nthought of a patient dying
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.50,0:28:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before you've been\Nable to figure out why.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.42,0:28:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're gonna keep refusing\Nto cure patients just to rein in my ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.53,0:28:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then we might start to have a\Nlittle problem with patient recruitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.37,0:28:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worried about meeting\Nyour one patient a week quota?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.95,0:28:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a cripple, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.03,0:28:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Accommodations must be made.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.32,0:29:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wedge of left lobe isolated
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.63,0:29:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.86,0:29:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.73,0:29:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you have me look up that article?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.49,0:29:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you find it interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.81,0:29:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He injected newborn babies\Nwith radioactive agents just to see
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.80,0:29:27.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- if they had urethral reflux.\N- He was curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.20,0:29:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't even tell their\Nparents he was doing an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.68,0:29:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't doing anything\Nhis peers weren't doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.79,0:29:33.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His peers at Tuskegee and Willowbrook?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.01,0:29:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He ignored the rights\Nof a few to save many.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.92,0:29:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're okay with what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't matter what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.60,0:29:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's what you think that's relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.28,0:29:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because if I think less of him,\NI'll help you more?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.63,0:29:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.70,0:29:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that a patient did\Nbad things doesn't change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.51,0:29:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He still deserves to have\Nsome control over his own body.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.43,0:29:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had control of his own body,\Nhe'd be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.03,0:30:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some control. We can withhold\Ntreatment without killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.45,0:30:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.58,0:30:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You either help him live, or you help\Nhim die. You can't have it both ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.74,0:30:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's not IPF.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.32,0:30:22.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe he'll die right now,\Nand make everything easy for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.80,0:30:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Heart rate's fast.\N- BP's low.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No breath sounds on the right side.\NHe's dropped his right lung.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.67,0:30:38.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Air's building up in his chest,\Ncompressing his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.38,0:30:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Heart rate's decreasing.\N- BP's stabilizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.55,0:31:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.42,0:31:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Withdraws from pain stimuli\Non the left side, but not the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.94,0:31:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are just reflex arcs.\NHe's under anesthesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.83,0:31:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or he's lost sensation in some places.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.52,0:31:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the hypoxia from\Nthe arrest stunned his CNS.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.37,0:31:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one way to tell.\NDo somatosensory evoked potentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.08,0:31:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't do that while he's in a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.85,0:31:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only two ways to tell. Get a hammer\Nand check his deep tendon reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.31,0:31:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't work. He needs muscle\Nrelaxants to be on the ventilator.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.66,0:31:49.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one more way to tell.\NPupillary reflexes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.42,0:31:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All that tests is the brainstem.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.92,0:31:52.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I was right. Only one way to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.71,0:31:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do somatosensory evoked potentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.55,0:31:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just said we can't\Ndo that while he's in a coma.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.78,0:31:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.48,0:32:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go towards the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.97,0:32:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll fall and break your hip.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.78,0:32:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.79,0:32:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took a little nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.87,0:32:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.18,0:32:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you I didn't want--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.37,0:32:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, a little deaf in one ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.91,0:32:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your bone marrow was hypocellular.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.06,0:33:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruled out lupus and pulmonary fibrosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.37,0:33:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it looks like it could\Nbe attacking your nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.56,0:33:07.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is all a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.93,0:33:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huge failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.19,0:33:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.97,0:33:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Gregory House.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.96,0:33:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to attach some\Nsensors to your skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.36,0:33:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No.\N- Look, we can't do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.26,0:33:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've assigned a nurse to\Nwatch you so you can't do it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.06,0:33:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you might as well\Njust let us do the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.86,0:33:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- No, I want to be discharged.\N- You can't be discharged.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.25,0:33:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You've got two chest tubes in.\N- Then take them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.94,0:33:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, get over yourself.\NThe ventilator puffed up your lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.48,0:33:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine for a few hours.\NJust let us run the tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.46,0:33:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.95,0:33:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But first, let's clean you up a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.47,0:33:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that feel nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.55,0:33:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What are you trying to prove?\N- Just cleaning him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.85,0:33:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.86,0:33:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay no attention to\Nthe man behind the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.86,0:34:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.74,0:34:06.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'm going already.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.08,0:34:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see I'm a cripple?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.25,0:34:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay, so you got me curious.\N- I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.94,0:34:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever is attacking his\Nlungs is attacking his nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.54,0:34:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that by splashing\Nice water on him?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.30,0:34:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No sensation in the left leg, abdomen,\Nright arm. Technology's overrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.60,0:34:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the clean MRI of\Nhis brain means it's just affecting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.16,0:34:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- the peripheral nerves.\N- And bone marrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.03,0:34:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki's would explain\Nthe kidney failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.84,0:34:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Or lymphoma.\N- Or sarcoidosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.96,0:34:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All potentially treatable.\NQuestion is which.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.08,0:34:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to catch the\Nlittle bastards in the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.22,0:34:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What's the largest organ?\N- Skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.21,0:34:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.48,0:34:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, we'll just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.49,0:34:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wait until he leaves his room without\Nhis skin, sneak in, and take a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.46,0:34:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to get a\Nskin sample for a biopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.59,0:34:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I want to get a foot\Nmassage from Johnny Damon.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.66,0:34:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki's disease, lymphoma,\Nand sarcoidosis are all treatable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.90,0:35:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it could be 100 other things\Nthat aren't treatable. You've no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.46,0:35:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.03,0:35:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I didn't say that I--\N- Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.82,0:35:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't decide if we're\Nhelping or hurting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.64,0:35:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.82,0:35:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or if you want paper,\Nplastic, or a burlap sack.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.04,0:35:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do your damn job.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.14,0:35:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna lie to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.20,0:35:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.31,0:35:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just get me a pound of flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.27,0:35:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.43,0:35:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,House wants to biopsy your skin.\NHe sent me to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.63,0:35:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, and you agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.85,0:35:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had nothing to do with putting you in\Na coma, or any of the subsequent tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.64,0:35:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which brings us to now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.44,0:35:49.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I read some of your articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.69,0:35:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were a lot of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.67,0:35:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1967 Massachusetts medical journal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.45,0:36:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You radiated babies, just like that.\NNo forms, no questions, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.66,0:36:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows how many cancers you caused?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.39,0:36:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.22,0:36:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I do know is we\Ndiscovered techniques that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.78,0:36:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,prevent fatal kidney failures\Nin hundreds of thousands of other kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.78,0:36:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're not sorry.\N- I don't regret what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.07,0:36:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Informed consent,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.61,0:36:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,patient rights
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.32,0:36:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,holds back research.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.27,0:36:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.87,0:36:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Informed consent is\Nholding back our diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.80,0:36:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.80,0:36:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally standing up for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.98,0:36:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Acting on what you believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.34,0:36:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. House?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.09,0:36:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.55,0:36:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Not as good as you think I am.\N- Don't worry, I'm not stalking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.89,0:36:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad just lost his medicine. He had\Nto come back for another prescription.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.86,0:36:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.46,0:37:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's moving it on the street, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.16,0:37:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, my dad, the meth kingpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.34,0:37:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why haven't you returned\Nany of my calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.59,0:37:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I plan to.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.28,0:37:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In a couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.79,0:37:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just calling to say thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.01,0:37:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to tell you how impressed I was. You\Ndiagnosed my dad by just looking at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.25,0:37:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Felt his glands too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.37,0:37:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's my dad. I gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.68,0:37:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah, me too.\N- Oh, and
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.99,0:37:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you really don't have to wait\Na couple years to return my calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.86,0:37:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.28,0:37:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Till I turn 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.08,0:37:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Kawasaki's either. What's next?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.70,0:37:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Congo red.\N- Amyloidosis?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.33,0:37:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell else\Nwould I mean by Congo red?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.54,0:37:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.51,0:37:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason\Nfor it to be on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.24,0:37:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An abnormal protein is building\Nup inside the cells of his body,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.36,0:38:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shutting down his organs, one by one.\NExplains everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.90,0:38:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the infiltrates on the x-ray,\Nthe bone marrow, kidney failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.60,0:38:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We rejected amyloidosis because it\Ndidn't fit the first symptom we found.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.94,0:38:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It would affect his heart.\N- It did.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.49,0:38:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- It wasn't on the stress test.\N- We didn't push him hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.59,0:38:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Add the stain, let's find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.67,0:38:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congo red added.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.98,0:38:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change the polarization\Nof the light already.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.46,0:38:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means it should be treatable.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.01,0:38:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- How the hell did you pull that out of\N- Not out of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.48,0:38:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a muse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.51,0:38:39.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, god.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.44,0:38:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Protein type AA.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.35,0:39:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dr. House--\N- You have amyloidosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.98,0:39:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in your lungs,\Nkidneys, bone marrow, and brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.30,0:39:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I believe you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.04,0:39:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I was lying,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.67,0:39:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't tell you the subtype is AA.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.79,0:39:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's terminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.69,0:39:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.91,0:39:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.13,0:40:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fresno by night.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.96,0:40:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Six months and counting.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.39,0:41:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ezra Powell passed away last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.65,0:41:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure you\Nalready knew about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.27,0:41:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. I just got in.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.45,0:41:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The nurse charted at 2:00 AM he was\Nstable. Breathing labored, but regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.55,0:41:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then at 2:30, he suddenly stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.60,0:41:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know anything about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.14,0:41:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.68,0:41:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you really want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.08,0:42:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,9:59:59.30,9:59:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Transcript: ydy.com - Synchro: jh26\NResynced for HDTV by NIZ